    "en": {
      "title": "Two crore gold and silver jewelery seized",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "A Sri Lankan business woman who illegally brought silver ornaments and jewelery worth two million and thirty three lakh rupees from India to Sri Lanka has been arrested by a group of customs officers at the arrival terminal of Katunayake Airport this morning.",
        "She is a 38-year-old businesswoman residing in the Grandpass area of \u200b\u200bColombo. She had arrived at the Katunayake airport at 02.45 this morning from Chennai, India, on the AI-273 flight of the Indian Airlines.",
        "While she was carrying a stock of jewelery weighing 01 kg and 638 grams and a stock of silver jewelery weighing 01 kg and 600 grams, the customs officers found them and arrested them.",
        "Ordered confiscation of all jewelery and ordered her to pay a fine of Rs 30,000."
      ],
